         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... by the Apsaras. (By) the gratitude of the Bodhisattva ... was destroyed. This Jambudvīpa [world] expanded immensely ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>403</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">flowers (rain)ed onto the humans. (1.) Queen ...mahī (bore (?)) the seed of Buddhahood proper to a Bodhisattva ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>358</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>56</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">she was honored [lit. in honor] by everyone including the gods. In [the tune] sruñcaññe: She remained happy, she slept happily ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>505</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>56</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>238</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (she was) provided with happiness. She rejoiced the receivers like the goddess Śrī, like an Apsaras goddess ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>305</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[the embryo] was [for ten months] concealed in the cavity of the belly; but through compassion [and] gratitude he mo(ved) to the city of the Saṃsāra without obstacle ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>52, 242</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... The Bodhisattvas (progress) through five births. [Like] a lotus flower stands in a pond, the Bodhisattva [rises] in ... . ... the evil ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">in order to make suffering disappear for the (beings). 1. Thereupon this glorious being together with the five (supernatural powers) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>198</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>277</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>260</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">in the hand of the ... he looked charming beyond measure. In [the tune] tuṣitabhavana: The earth trembled. It went (to the six directions) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>713</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they made visible the (cintāmaṇi jewe)l (?) in front of him. The sages in the forests provided with five supernatural powers went to see him. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>736</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1960a"/><citedRange>202</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">The king Viśvāmitra having ordered to call forth the Brahmins that have understood the omen, the divine ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>478</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">« Oh teacher, having interpreted the glorious signs of my son, as a consequence of that give him a name! » Thereupon the Bra(hmins say: ...)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they will go out. The king says: « My son A., (fullfill)ing (the wish) ... the cintāmaṇi jewel ... »</seg></seg></choice></p>
